by airplane! This was the funniest thing I have done in a long time. I think going to the grocery in a boat is not that fun. But on a plane is definitely more fun.

Of course to do this, I needed the Airport Authority to agree to let me use my safety-approved wristbands on the airplane. After all, even with Dhives it seems they are very strict with safety – so much so that we had to switch seats many times in the plane just to make sure there is no overloading. That is something I am glad with. The last time I flew, in US, the plane was half full but I was still overloaded with people in one of the seats. I will never understand how in America you are allowed to sit with 3 or 4 across and get killed when you land, or if it is an emergency parachute jump. I guess reimbursements go a long way in boosting the market I suppose.

Also sometimes I even hate my father. I should have never met the people I did with the one type of education I had. If I had met a better type of Elie, it would be possible through internet. Only of course, maybe I should give a little choice to people who would not know what to do with me. I'd rather work on a school project on vacation, than spend my vacation on a Nerf project. Actually, that sounds fun! All the best from 3 Easy Steps Many are not as well
